Key Match Events: The Padres evened up the series at 1-1 with a 10-2 win over the Dodgers.
Jurickson Profar robbed Mookie Betts of a home run by reaching into the stands to make the catch in left field.
Fernando Tatis Jr. homered earlier in the game and could be seen fully embracing the boos from Dodgers fans as he danced around in right field.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was delayed after fans hurled objects onto the field, targeting Padres outfielders Jurickson Profar and Fernando Tatis Jr.
The delay in the action lasted roughly 12 minutes as stadium security attempted to identify the troublemakers.
